<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>As stated by Kerridwynn Spellbender, Ilharess</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
I.  Conduct Outside of the Guildhall<br>
<br>
All guild members must realize that their actions directly effect the guild reputation.  As this is a fact, the following is not condoned:<br>
<br>
~  Taunting, teasing, and seducing a creature from another in order to destroy it yourself.  (Killstealing)<br>
<br>
~  Deliberately bringing about the death of another by luring creatures down upon them. (Training)<br>
<br>
~  Engaging in past-times that the gods find distasteful and wrong.  (Breaking any of the rest of SoE's rules of conduct)<br>
<br>
If a member is caught doing any of these three things, they are subject to immediate removal from the Harvesters of Darkness.  There will be no discussions had, excuses made, or leniancy given.  Do not test the resolve of myself, or the officers serving under me, on these issues.<br>
<br>
If it is eluded to that a member has done any of these things, that member will be questioned and watched.  I do not believe the word of outsiders over the word of my guildmembers, but I am not naive either.  My word will be final in these cases.<br>
<br>
II.  Conduct Within the Guildhall<br>
<br>
Dealings within the Guildhall amongst bretheren of the Scythe must always be <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">respectful</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.  Should there be an issue that neither party can handle in a mature fashion, it will be dealt with by myself or an officer, most notably the guild Enforcer.<br>
<br>
The Guildhall is not a stable, an arena, or a dwarven tavern.  I expect all roughhousing, brawls, target practice, horseback riding, spellcasting, tests of strength, etc to be conducted outside of the Guildhall in the areas provided for such.<br>
<br>
III.  Guild Requirements for Members and Prospective Members<br>
<br>
The most important quality we seek in our members is <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">loyalty</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.  Loyalty to the ideals of the Scythe, loyalty to the Ilharess, and loyalty to the brethren of the Scythe. <br>
<br>
Other qualities we seek are open-mindedness, basic grasp of social manners, maturity, determination, steadfastness.  It will not hurt for you to know the basic ins and outs of your profession.  <br>
<br>
Do not come seeking entry to our halls expecting an easy road to prowess (powerleveling).  However, you may find instructors who will help you along your way.  <br>
<br>
There is no set policy of handing down gifts, but it does and will occur.  Many of our bretheren would rather see an old weapon or other possession in use by a guildmate rather than sold.  Should you accept such a token, be sure to return it when you have outstripped its usefullness, unless otherwise told.  It is the decent thing to do.<br>
<br>
IV.  Guild Policies:  Our Place in Norrath<br>
<br>
~  We are the Harvesters of Darkness.  We have a unique position within the world.  The Scythe is made up of people who have varying opinions, stances, and creeds but still manage to live with, strive with, and befriend eachother.  It is a place of understanding, a place where we are free to think as we will free of the fear of reprisals from those we trust and admire.  We are of the dark community, but forever removed from it.  We are the outcasts.  We are the rebels.  We are the fringes of society, and we rejoice.<br>
<br>
~  Do as you will.  Kill lightbringers should that make you happy.  Kill halflings if you want toes for baking.  Befriend a wood elf and spend time hugging trees with them.  Have tea with a high elf.  The Scythe will not prohibit you from doing any of these things, for it will not infringe upon your personal choices, unless these choices happens to be one of the three cardinal sins mentioned above in section I.  Do not expect to be utterly free from the consequences of your choices however.  There are reactions to every action, and you must take personal responsibility in all things.  There is no blame game within the Scythe.<br>
<br>
V.  Guild Policies: Recruitment<br>
<br>
Read the criteria before applying.  Anything not mentioned as acceptable is not and will not be considered.  There has been some question as to whether the Harvesters is an evil guild or not. Here, in detail, are the races and professions we accept:<br>
<br>
No dwarves, high elves, wood elves, halflings. Ever. For any reason.<br>
<br>
No rangers, druids, paladins or bards. Ever. For any reason.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Clerics</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->~ Human if you follow Innoruuk or Bertox. Teir'dal. Gnome if you follow Bertox. Erudite if you follow Cazic-Thule.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Shaman</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->~ Iksar (if you're not a Cabilis loyalist), Ogre, Troll. Barbarians and Vah Shir on a case by case basis.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Beastlord</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->~ Iksar, Ogre, Troll. Vah Shir on a case by case basis.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Warrior</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->~ Human if you follow Bertox, Innoruuk, or Rallos. Halfelf if you follow Bertox, Innoruuk, or Rallos. Teir'dal. Ogre. Troll. Iksar. Gnome if you follow Bertox or Rallos. Barbarian if you follow Rallos. Vah Shir on a case by case basis.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Necromancer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->~ Any race who can be one.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Shadow Knight</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->~ Any race who can be one.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Rogue</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->~ Human if you follow Bertox or Innoruuk. Halfelves if you follow Bertox. Gnome if you follow Bertox. Teir'dal. Barbarian and Vah Shir on a case by case basis.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Enchanters</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->~ Human if you follow Bertox or Innoruuk. Gnome if you follow Bertox. Teir'dal.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Magician</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->~ Human if you follow Bertox or Innoruuk. Gnome if you follow Bertox. Tier'dal.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Wizard</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->~ Human if you follow Bertox, Innoruuk, or Solusek Ro. Erudite if you follow Solusek Ro. Gnome if you follow Bertox or Solusek Ro.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Monk</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->~ Iksar and agnostic humans<br>
<br>
All other agnostics will be taken on a case by case basis as long as you don't fall under one of the restricted races or classes.<br>
